sql:
SELECT title, upload_date, price
FROM art_pieces
WHERE medium = 'Oil on Canvas' AND CAST(price AS REAL) > 1000;

external_knowledge:
- "Most recently uploaded" refers to the latest `upload_date` for each artist;
- "Added to collections" means the art pieces are included in user collections;
- "Most popular" is determined by the number of distinct users who have added the art piece to their collections.

- 'Enchanted treasures' refers to art pieces;
- 'Mystical series' refers to the specific series with series_id = 1;
- 'Adorned with the mark of fantasy' refers to art pieces tagged with 'Fantasy'.

- "Shining star" refers to the artist with the highest average rating;
- "Standing out" implies the artist must have an average rating greater than 3;
- "Active collaborations" means the artist has more than 2 collaborations.

- "a chorus of praise" refers to an average rating greater than 3;
- "a flurry of comments" refers to more than 5 comments;
- "a price that speaks of their value" refers to art pieces priced over $100;
- "the most distinguished artist" refers to the artist ID selected in the final query, ordered by artist ID in descending order and limited to the top result.

- "prolific" refers to having created more than 5 art pieces;
- "collaborative" refers to having participated in more than 2 collaborations;
- "high acclaim" refers to an average rating greater than 4;
- "richly tagged" refers to having more than 10 tags associated with their art pieces.

- The 'total value' of a series is calculated by summing the prices of all art pieces within that series;
- The 'average rating' is the mean of all ratings given to the art pieces in the series;
- 'Collections' refer to series of art pieces;
- 'Treasure' refers to the total value of the art pieces in each series.

- "Threads in the tapestry of collaboration" refers to the number of collaborations an artist has been involved in;
- "Woven" is a metaphor for participating in collaborations;
- "The most threads" indicates the highest number of collaborations.

- `artist_id` 1 refers to a specific artist in the database;
- `series_id` and `series_name` are unique identifiers and names for different series of art pieces;
- `description` provides a narrative or explanation about each series.

sql:
SELECT title, price
FROM art_pieces
WHERE price = (SELECT MIN(price) FROM art_pieces);

SELECT COUNT(art_id) 
FROM art_piece_tags 
WHERE tag_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed under the attention" refers to art pieces that have received multiple forms of engagement, such as ratings and comments;
- "admirers" refers to users who have interacted with the art pieces;
- "ratings and comments" are the forms of engagement recorded in the `ratings` and `comments` tables.

- 'Highly rated artists' refers to artists whose art pieces have the highest average ratings;
- 'Art pieces priced over $100' filters out any art pieces that are $100 or less;
- 'Top 10' refers to the artists with the highest average ratings, ranked in descending order.

- 'Collaborators' refer to artists who have worked together on creating art pieces;
- The 'hierarchy' of artists is based on the level of collaboration, where top-level artists are those who have not been a secondary collaborator;
- 'Unique artists' means each artist is counted only once per art piece, regardless of the number of times they have collaborated on it.

- "unveiled recently" refers to the most recently uploaded art pieces, ordered by `upload_date` in descending order;
- "artists behind them" refers to the usernames of the artists who created the art pieces;
- "themes they explore" refers to the categories associated with each art piece;
- "value they command" refers to the price of the art piece;
- "applause they receive" refers to the average rating of the art piece, with 0 if no ratings are available.

- "Collaborations" refer to instances where artists have worked together on art pieces;
- "High average rating" is defined as having an average rating greater than 10;
- "Multiple categories" means the artist has produced art in more than 2 different categories.

- 'Most prolific artists' refers to artists with the highest number of art pieces;
- 'Top-rated art piece' is determined by the highest average rating;
- 'Collaboration count' is the number of unique collaborations an artist has participated in.
